LAT101H1-F-20219.courseDescription: An intensive introduction to Latin for students who have no knowledge of the language; preparation for the reading of Latin literature.
LAT101H1-F-20219.exclusion: LAT100Y1. Students who have studied Latin previously must obtain permission from the Undergraduate Coordinator before enrolling.

LAT101H1-S-20219.courseDescription: An intensive introduction to Latin for students who have no knowledge of the language; preparation for the reading of Latin literature.
LAT101H1-S-20219.exclusion: LAT100Y1. Students who have studied Latin previously must obtain permission from the Undergraduate Coordinator before enrolling.

LAT102H1-S-20219.courseDescription: A continuation of the intensive introduction to Latin in LAT 101H1. Also appropriate for students who have some training in Latin, but have not completed a whole credit course at University or a final-year (Grade 12) course in secondary school.

LAT201H1-F-20219.courseDescription: Reading of selections of Latin prose works with systematic language study.
LAT201H1-F-20219.prerequisite: LAT100Y1/LAT102H1. Grade 12 in Latin may be accepted, but students should consult the Undergraduate Coordinator before enrolling.

LAT202H1-S-20219.courseDescription: Continued language training with readings in Latin prose and verse.

LAT341H1-F-20219.courseDescription: Readings from one or more Latin historians.

LAT343H1-S-20219.courseDescription: Readings from Latin prose authors (e. g. biography, letters, philosophy).

LAT353H1-S-20219.courseDescription: Readings from Latin verse (e. g. elegy, lyric, bucolic).

LAT428H1-F-20219.courseDescription: Independent Studies. Not eligible for CR/NCR option.

LAT429H1-F-20219.courseDescription: Independent Studies. Not eligible for CR/NCR option.

LAT429H1-S-20219.courseDescription: Independent Studies. Not eligible for CR/NCR option.

LAT430H1-S-20219.courseDescription: A course designed to enhance language skills. Prose composition, sight translation, stylistic analysis of Latin prose.

LAT441H1-F-20219.courseDescription: Advanced readings from one or more Latin historians.
LAT441H1-F-20219.deliveryInstructions: We shall read the beginning and end of Book 1 of Livy, Ab urbe condita, and Suetonius, Life of Divus Claudius, with an emphasis on language and style, but not without attention to historiography and history. Specific to LAT 441 are sections from Tacitus, Annales Book 1.

LAT443H1-S-20219.courseDescription: Advanced readings from Latin prose authors (e. g. biography, letters, philosophy).

LAT451H1-F-20219.courseDescription: Advanced readings from Latin comedy and/or tragedy.

LAT453H1-S-20219.courseDescription: Advanced readings from Latin verse (e. g. elegy, lyric, bucolic).
